 # https://tools.ietf.org/id/draft-miller-ssh-agent-00.html

ssh-agent key blob format:
    http://twistedmatrix.com/documents/8.2.0/api/twisted.conch.ssh.keys.Key.html#blob

(n,e) -> PEM:
    https://stackoverflow.com/questions/11541192/creating-a-rsa-public-key-from-its-modulus-and-exponent

http://krisjordan.com/essays/encrypting-with-rsa-key-pairs

PKCS8 format:
https://unix.stackexchange.com/a/358709/233034

...nope, while it's possible to get the public key from the ssh-agent, and to
use that key to encrypt data using RSA, there's no corresponding ssh-agent
function for taking encrypted data and decrypting it in the agent.
